## Specs-R1 — Spec Conversion Gap Audit (Post-Write)
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:frontend

After converting `docs/design/forge-specs-relay-frontend.md` into formal specs, a gap audit identified missing component designs and an undocumented SSE routing contract.

| Gap | Severity | Resolution | Location |
|---||---|---|
| `GateBanner` component (Specs view sticky gate banner) | High | New Design Specs-D3 | `designs.ad` |
| `GatePanel` component (Relay view gate approval) | High | New Design Relay-D9 | `designs.ad` |
| `ReportCard` component (terminal completion in chat) | High | New Design Chat-D2 | `designs.ad` |
| SSE Event Map / Frontend Integration | Critical | New Design Relay-D10 | `designs.ad` |
| Open questions untracked (sound, escalation, persistence, locking) | Medium | Added as plan risks | `plans.ad` (Chat-P1, Relay-P9, UiSystem-P1) |

- Sound design: opt-in chime for gates?
- Gate escalation: browser notification after >30min?
- Secretary queue persistence across refresh (backend dependency)
- Multi-run document locking (ETag strategy)

All P0 gaps are now closed. The 4 new designs (Specs-D3–Relay-D10) and 3 additional plan risks provide sufficient detail for the Coder to begin implementation.

